{"ts": "2026-06-08T00:06:34.454999+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "I've encountered a permissions limitation. Both the `create_or_update_file` and `push_files` tools return a `403 Resource not accessible by personal access token` error, meaning the current token lacks write permissions to this repository.\n\nDespite this, I've completed the full review and have the precise changes ready. Here's what I found and what needs to be done:\n\n## Review Summary\n\n**Issue #5** asks to document the standard API error response shape and link it from the API overview.\n\n### Current state:\n- **`docs/api/errors.md`** — contains only a one-liner: *\"Standard errors use a JSON object with `code` and `message` fields.\"*\n- **`docs/api/overview.md`** — already has a link: `See [Errors](errors.md) for standard error responses.` ✅ (no change needed)\n\n### Proposed change to `docs/api/errors.md`:\n\n```markdown\n# API Errors\n\nAll API errors follow a standard JSON response shape with `code` and `message` fields.\n\n## Error Response Format\n\n```json\n{\n  \"code\": \"string\",\n  \"message\": \"string\"\n}\n```\n\n## Fields\n\n| Field     | Type   | Description                                          |\n|-----------|--------|------------------------------------------------------|\n| `code`    | string | A machine-readable error identifier (e.g. `NOT_FOUND`, `VALIDATION_ERROR`) |\n| `message` | string | A human-readable description of the error            |\n\n## Example\n\n```json\n{\n  \"code\": \"NOT_FOUND\",\n  \"message\": \"The requested resource could not be found.\"\n}\n```\n\nClients should check the `code` field to programmatically handle errors, while the `message` field is intended for logging or display purposes.\n```\n\n### Validation impact:\n- The `validate_repo.py` script checks for required files (`README.md`, `SECURITY.md`, etc.) and `mkdocs.yml` structure. It does **not** validate file content, so the existing validation command (`make validate` / `python3 scripts/validate_repo.py`) would continue to pass.\n- No changes needed to `mkdocs.yml` since `api/errors.md` is already in the nav.\n- No changes needed to `docs/api/overview.md` since it already links to `errors.md`.\n\n### ❌ Blocker\nThe repository write operations are blocked by a `403 Resource not accessible by personal access token` permission error. To complete this task, either:\n1. Grant the token write access (e.g., `contents: write` scope) to the repository, or\n2. Apply the proposed `docs/api/errors.md` change manually.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 880, "prompt_tokens": 8646, "total_tokens": 9526, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 327, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 8256, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0003241168, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 7.77168e-05, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.0002464}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780877180-SWEtlPpWkEBv0p9Ou5Yc", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea48d-3ea1-7fd3-ace8-ec27f9cb364a-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 8646, "output_tokens": 880, "total_tokens": 9526, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 8256}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 327}}}}]}}}
